definition.value: A group obtained by removing the hydroxy group from the hemiacetal function of beta-D-galactosyl-(1->3)-[alpha-L-fucosyl-(1->4)]-N-acetyl-D-glucosamine.
A group obtained by removing the hydroxy group from the hemiacetal function of beta-D-galactosyl-(1->3)-N-acetyl-D-glucosamine.

A secondary alcohol that is isopropanol in which one hydrogen of each methyl group is substituted by a chlorine. A liquid at room temperature (melting point -4degreeC, boiling point 174degreeC at 760 mm Hg), it is used as a solvent for hard resins and nitrocellulose.
A chloropropene with two chloro substituents at positions 1 and 3 respectively..
